                        Morris
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d529</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">529</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-01-19T09:35:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-01-19T09:35:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-19T09:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-19T09:35:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-19T18:00:00+03:25">January 19, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. ReEmbs 30, January 17. Bayat has written Millspaugh sharp reply<note n="13" xml:id="d529fn13">Dated January 18. Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Ambassador in Iran in despatch 185, January 24, 1945; neither
                        printed.</note> to his letter regarding Ebtehaj dispute. Prime Minister
                    flatly rejects Millspaugh demand that Ebtehaj be removed or at least suspended
                    and suggests that if Millspaugh still insists he should have matter referred to
                    Majlis through Finance Minister.<note n="14" xml:id="d529fn14">Amanollah
                        Ardalan.</note>
                </p>
                <p>As yet Millspaugh who has been ill for several days has said nothing to me
                    regarding his plans in light of this development.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
